.TH "hash_disable_power" 9 "hash_disable_power" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hash_disable_power \- Request to disable power and clock.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hash_disable_power
.BI "(struct hash_device_data *device_data "  ","
.BI "bool save_device_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device_data" 12
Structure for the hash device.
.IP "save_device_state" 12
If true, saves the current hw state.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function request for disabling power (regulator) and clock,
and could also save current hw state.
